# Caution Resolve Scoping

Multiple features can add caution reasons to the same page (e.g. nav migration adds "Link integrity may need attention", dead link finder adds "Internal dead links found" / "External dead links found"). When a feature resolves its own cautions, it must **only remove its own reasons** — never clear the entire caution entry or wipe all cautions indiscriminately.

## Rules

1. **Remove only your reasons.** When resolving a caution, filter out only the reason strings your feature created. Use `_stripDeadLinkCautionReasons` or `_removeCautionReason` as the pattern — iterate `reasons[]`, splice only matching entries.

2. **Preserve the entry if other reasons remain.** After removing your reasons, check if `reasons.length` is still > 0. Only delete the caution entry and remove the nav icon when the array is empty.

3. **Never call `_setCautionPages([])` from feature-specific resolve.** Clearing all cautions is only acceptable for an explicit "Resolve All Cautions" action in the caution popup itself, not from feature panels like the dead link panel.

4. **Nav icon removal requires empty reasons.** Only remove `.live-wysiwyg-nav-caution` icon and `.live-wysiwyg-nav-caution-item` class when the page's caution entry is fully deleted (no reasons left from any feature).

5. **Each feature owns its reason strings.** Document which reason strings a feature uses so other features don't accidentally match them. Current inventory:
   - Nav migration: `"Link integrity may need attention"`
   - Dead link finder: `"Internal dead links found"`, `"External dead links found"`
   - Unreferenced asset finder: `"Unreferenced asset"`

## Related

Cautions interact with **Nav Renderer** (navData + snapshots) and **Application Storage** (localStorage persistence). See `docs/design/backend/DESIGN-cautions.md` for the full design document.
